law.text:
A person is guilty of possession of stolen mail matter when he knowingly or having reason to believe that it has been the subject of theft in violation of KRS 514.140:
Possesses;
Buys;
Receives;
Conceals;
Deals in; or
Sells; any mail matter (as defined in KRS 514.140).
Possession of stolen mail matter is a Class D felony.
